# Research the Existing Stream Ingress

## Question

Ground truth for "how do webhooks flow into memory": where do Front and
Slack realtime updates actually land today (gateway channels? Inngest
functions? ClickHouse tables? Redis? dropped on the floor?) — exact code
paths in joelclaw (packages/gateway, packages/system-bus), event shapes,
volumes/day per source, retention, and what ClickHouse currently holds.
Also inventory the Bugle's existing source adapters (which of
Front/Slack/GitHub/Twitter it already reads at build time, and how).
Receipts per claim. Output: a coverage matrix svx in .brain/resources/
— the epoch-model and quality grillings are blocked on this.

## Resolution (2026-07-13)

Full matrix: [stream-ingress-inventory-2026-07](../../resources/stream-ingress-inventory-2026-07.svx).
Headlines: (1) Front webhooks LIVE at the edge (274/day) but durable
downstream UNPROVEN — projections stale since 2026-05-31; lifecycle events
may terminate in Inngest with no consumer. (2) Slack realtime is DEAD —
0 events in 30 days, gateway daemon unreachable on flagg; historical
backfill frozen at 2026-04-29. (3) ClickHouse is 99.78% a
redis.subscriber.error storm (102M of 102.3M rows) — a poisoned telemetry
sink, not a message archive. (4) The Bugle collects Front/GitHub/X at
edition time, never Slack. Graduated: three repair tasks; the three
grillings unblock with this ground truth.
